<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">Found on the rhodoliths surface.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">Remarks</emphasis>
: This species already has been recorded for the northeast Brazilian (
<bibRefCitation author="Amaral, A. Cecilia Z." journalOrPublisher="UNICAMP, Campinas" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" refId="B6420637" refString="Amaral, A. Cecilia Z., Nallin, Silvana A. Henriques, Steiner, Tatiana Menchini, Forroni, Thalita Oliveira, Filho, Decio Gomes, 2013. Catalogo das especies de Annelida Polychaeta do Brasil. UNICAMP, Campinas" title="Catalogo das especies de Annelida Polychaeta do Brasil" year="2013">Amaral et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa, Dimitri Araujo" journalOrPublisher="Revista Brasileira de Gestao Ambiental e Sustentabilidade" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" pagination="313 - 320" refId="B6421986" refString="Costa, Dimitri Araujo, Fernandes, Helder Formiga, Silva, Francisco Assis, Christoffersen, Martin Lindsey, 2017. Checklist of species of Polychaeta (Annelida) of the Seixas Beach, Joao Pessoa, state of Paraiba, Northeast Brazil. Revista Brasileira de Gestao Ambiental e Sustentabilidade 4 (8): 313 - 320" title="Checklist of species of Polychaeta (Annelida) of the Seixas Beach, Joao Pessoa, state of Paraiba, Northeast Brazil" volume="4" year="2017">Costa et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
) and confirmed with morphological description in previous studies (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa, Dimitri Araujo" journalOrPublisher="Biociencias (on-line)" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" pagination="131 - 133" refId="B6421977" refString="Costa, Dimitri Araujo, DeAssis, Jose Eriberto, Christoffersen, Martin Lindsey, 2008. New synonym of Hesione splendida (Hesionidae, Polychaeta, Annelida). Biociencias (on-line) 16 (2): 131 - 133" title="New synonym of Hesione splendida (Hesionidae, Polychaeta, Annelida)" volume="16" year="2008">Costa et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa, Dimitri Araujo" journalOrPublisher="Gaia Scientia" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" pagination="166 - 172" refId="B6421968" refString="Costa, Dimitri Araujo, Christoffersen, Martin Lindsey, 2016. Revision and global distribution of Hesione splendida (Annelida, Polychaeta, Hesionidae). Gaia Scientia 10 (4): 166 - 172" title="Revision and global distribution of Hesione splendida (Annelida, Polychaeta, Hesionidae)" volume="10" year="2016">Costa and Christoffersen 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Notwithstanding, a molecular identification is required and a systematic analysis comparing the genetic distances amongst the species of this genus. For this moment, we continue to consider it as 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Chironomidae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. splendida" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="splendida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">H. splendida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">
(
<bibRefCitation author="Costa, Dimitri Araujo" journalOrPublisher="Biociencias (on-line)" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" pagination="131 - 133" refId="B6421977" refString="Costa, Dimitri Araujo, DeAssis, Jose Eriberto, Christoffersen, Martin Lindsey, 2008. New synonym of Hesione splendida (Hesionidae, Polychaeta, Annelida). Biociencias (on-line) 16 (2): 131 - 133" title="New synonym of Hesione splendida (Hesionidae, Polychaeta, Annelida)" volume="16" year="2008">Costa et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa, Dimitri Araujo" journalOrPublisher="Gaia Scientia" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" pagination="166 - 172" refId="B6421968" refString="Costa, Dimitri Araujo, Christoffersen, Martin Lindsey, 2016. Revision and global distribution of Hesione splendida (Annelida, Polychaeta, Hesionidae). Gaia Scientia 10 (4): 166 - 172" title="Revision and global distribution of Hesione splendida (Annelida, Polychaeta, Hesionidae)" volume="10" year="2016">Costa and Christoffersen 2016</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Imajima, Minoru" journalOrPublisher="National Science Museum Monographs" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" pagination="1 - 221" refId="B6422669" refString="Imajima, Minoru, 2003. Polychaetous annelids from Sagami Bay and Sagami Sea collected by the Emperor Showa of Japan and deposited at the Showa Memorial Institute, National Science Museum, Tokyo (II): orders included within the Phyllodocida, Amphinomida, Spintherida and Eunicida. National Science Museum Monographs 23: 1 - 221" title="Polychaetous annelids from Sagami Bay and Sagami Sea collected by the Emperor Showa of Japan and deposited at the Showa Memorial Institute, National Science Museum, Tokyo (II): orders included within the Phyllodocida, Amphinomida, Spintherida and Eunicida" volume="23" year="2003">Imajima 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Salazar-Vallejo, Sergio I." journalOrPublisher="Zoosystema" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" pagination="227 - 325" refId="B6829589" refString="Salazar-Vallejo, Sergio I., 2018. Revision of Hesione Savigny in Lamarck, 1818 (Annelida, Errantia, Hesionidae). Zoosystema 40 (12): 227 - 325" title="Revision of Hesione Savigny in Lamarck, 1818 (Annelida, Errantia, Hesionidae)" volume="40" year="2018">Salazar-Vallejo 2018</bibRefCitation>
): Prostomium with four eyes, two papilla-like antennae, facial tubercle, nuchal organs and an incision in posterior end. Anterior proboscis ring smooth, carrying two black points in medium-lateral region and a tubercle in the median-posterior region. First segments with eight pairs of modified cirri (&quot;tentacular cirri&quot;) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStartId="F6439236" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">4</figureCitation>
<figureCitation captionStartId="F6439242" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">b</figureCitation>
). Parapodia sesquiramous-type (notopodial region reduced to cirri and no chaetae); neuropodia with falcigers and dark aciculae. Neurochaetal blades with two teeth-like processes anteriorly, up to 9 times longer than wide.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
